<br>
my worst nightmare are these wizard pets... I can just see a lvl 60 wizard running around in a dungeon with a pet on their ass aggroing everything under the sun, pet control is something that you learn as you level, having an instant pet and being in a lvl 60 dungeon is kind of dangerous.  Not saying wizards don't know pet control or can't learn, but I can just see wipeouts due to these familiars... <br>
<br>
and if you're in a dungeon and you're pet is missing and you see taunting attacker master... for the love of god don't invis yourself!  all that does is kill your pet and you'll have a train incoming.  If that happens, sit your ass down and camp out your aggro, and hope to god your pet holds the mob for 30 more seconds.  The only time you wanna invis is when your pet is missing, and you're NOT seeing taunting attacker master.  <br>
